<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.7141758>
    dc:description "FIGURE 2. Morphological characters of Craterium muscorum. a. Sporangia on bark. b. Sporangium was not broken to form a high cup-shaped sporangium (SEM). c. Peridium, stalk, and columella. d. Sporocarp showing the columella. e. Columella (arrow, SEM). f. Reticulate spores (LM). g. Capillitium (arrow, LM). h, i. Reticulate spores (SEM). j. Capillitium and columella connected with each other (arrow, SEM). k. Calcareous capillitium forming a whitish tridimensional net (SEM). Scale bars: a, c = 1 mm, b, e = 100 μm, d, f = 20 μm, g = 50 μm, h, i = 1 μm, j, k = 10 μm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/7141758/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

